  "prompt": "What are the 5 best Cirque du Soleil songs and from which show do they come?",
  "response": "Okay, narrowing down the \"best\" Cirque du Soleil songs is incredibly subjective, as there are so many amazing pieces and different people connect with different styles. However, based on popularity, critical acclaim, and lasting impact, here are 5 of the best Cirque du Soleil songs, along with their respective shows:\n\n1.  **\"Alegria\" - *Alegr\u00eda* (1994):** This is arguably the most iconic Cirque du Soleil song of all time. It is a powerful, emotionally stirring anthem that perfectly captures the show's themes of hope, rebirth, and the struggle between the old and the new. Its soaring vocals, haunting melodies, and grand orchestration made it instantly recognizable and enduringly popular. It is sung in Spanish.\n\n2.  **\"Adagio\" - *Saltimbanco* (1992):** *Saltimbanco* was groundbreaking for Cirque, and \"Adagio\" is a perfect example of that. It is not as popular as the first song on this list, but it is a beautiful and haunting melody. It is one of Cirque's most beautiful songs.\n\n3.  **\"Kumbalaw\u00e9\" - *O* (1998):** \"Kumbalaw\u00e9\" has a special place in fans' hearts for its infectious energy and unique vocal harmonies. It is sung in a made-up language, which perfectly complements the otherworldly and dreamlike quality of the show. It's a fun, upbeat number that stays with you long after you've heard it.\n\n4.  **\"Incantation\" - *Myst\u00e8re* (1993):** Incantation is an older song from one of Cirque's original shows, *Myst\u00e8re*, but it is a fan favorite due to its haunting tones and unique style.\n\n5.  **\"Se Bastasse Una Canzone\" - *QUIDAM* (1996):** Another incredibly beautiful and emotionally resonant song. *Quidam* is one of Cirque's darker shows, and this song is the perfect summary of the show's themes.\n\nUltimately, \"best\" is in the ear of the beholder. Cirque du Soleil has a vast and diverse musical catalog, and exploring it is a rewarding experience!\n",
